The term of decadence is part of the contraction 'modern ideas of decadence' or ‘what is at stake in the eternal recurrence of all’. For examples, the decline of art is a ‘redeem’ character of decadence. also, Brutality is the downfall of greatness but also of nobility; likewise, the historical sense involves the abandonment of one’s positive values but also of the idea of greatness. Thus, the historical self-overcoming of religion and values culminates in the ascetic ideal.

