The term of decadence is Brutality. Brutality is the end of what is left of art. Within the structure of art, the highest forms are always the slaves of chance, and the forces that have created the human soul. Within this structure, fate must be understood as the enemy and must bepped off by gratitude. The idea is that successfully defending art from attack of the impossible is the key to a deeper and more creative future.

